benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/renameKey - Update a bundle externalKey

covered: Valid Request: Scenario TC01 covers successful update with correct headers and body.
Missing required header: TC02 tests missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header.
Malformed bundleId: TC03 covers invalid bundleId format.
Non-existent bundleId: TC04 covers bundle not found scenario.
ExternalKey conflict: TC05 tests conflict when externalKey is already used.
Missing request body: TC06 covers missing body scenario.
Malformed JSON body: TC07 covers JSON parse errors.
Missing externalKey in body: TC08 tests validation for required externalKey.
Extra fields in body: TC09 tests handling of additional unexpected fields.
Long externalKey: TC10 covers extremely long externalKey input.
Empty externalKey: TC11 tests empty string validation.
Unauthorized access: TC12 covers missing/invalid auth token.
Service unavailable: TC13 covers system dependency failures.
Additional headers: TC14 tests optional headers like X-Killbill-Reason.
No bundles in system: TC15 covers empty database scenario.
Large payload: TC16 tests handling of big request bodies.
Concurrent updates: TC17 covers race conditions.
Regression test: TC18 for previously problematic externalKey.
Special characters: TC19 tests externalKey with special characters.
Leading/trailing spaces: TC20 tests validation/trimming rules.
Unexpected headers: TC21 tests extra headers handling.
Backward compatibility: TC22 covers legacy client requests.
Response time: TC23 measures performance under load.
Accessibility: TC24 ensures API documentation is accessible.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Authorization: No explicit tests for authorization beyond TC12.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios testing cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
System dependency failures: No detailed tests for database or service outages beyond TC13.
Edge case for maximum length externalKey beyond 255 characters is not explicitly tested.
No explicit tests for handling of special or invalid characters beyond basic scenarios.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling if the API supports listing bundles with large datasets.
Include explicit authorization tests for different user roles and tokens.
Implement rate limiting tests to verify system stability under high request volume.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behaviors.
Test maximum allowed length for externalKey to ensure system limits are enforced.
Include additional edge cases for special characters and invalid input formats.
